## Memory — Mindbrain

**Memory is managed by Mindbrain (cloud-persistent). Do NOT use MEMORY.md, auto-memory, or flat files.**

### CRITICAL: Use Mindbrain context FIRST
When answering questions, ALWAYS check your system-reminder for `[Mindbrain —` sections BEFORE exploring files. These contain verified project knowledge.

### Save memories
```bash
echo "content" | mb save "Title" -t TYPE --tags "tag1,tag2"
```
Types: `user`, `feedback`, `project`, `reference`, `codebase`, `debug`.

### Recall memories
```bash
mb search "query"
mb context -f file1 file2 -t "task description"
```

### When to save
- User corrects approach → `mb save -t feedback`
- User confirms approach → `mb save -t feedback`
- Architecture discovered → `mb save -t codebase`
- Project context → `mb save -t project`

**DO NOT save to `~/.claude/memory/` or MEMORY.md. Use `mb save` exclusively.**
